      "agentResultText": "All done. Here's a summary of what was set up:\n\n**Packages installed:** `prisma`, `@prisma/client`, `@prisma/adapter-pg`, `pg`, `dotenv`, `tsx`\n\n**Prisma schema** (`prisma/schema.prisma`) — 4 models:\n- `Organization` (id, name, slug) → has many Users and Projects\n- `User` (id, name, email, role, organizationId) → belongs to Organization, has many Tasks\n- `Project` (id, name, description, status, organizationId) → belongs to Organization, has many Tasks\n- `Task` (id, title, description, status, priority, dueDate, createdAt, projectId, assigneeId) → belongs to Project and optional User assignee\n\n**New files created:**\n- `src/lib/prisma.ts` — PrismaClient singleton with PG adapter\n- `prisma/seed.ts` — seeds all 22 tasks, 5 projects, 5 users, 3 orgs (matching original mock data)\n- `prisma/migrations/` — initial migration\n\n**Files updated (mock-data → Prisma queries):**\n- `src/app/dashboard/page.tsx` — uses `prisma.*.count()` for stats\n- `src/app/projects/page.tsx` — uses `findMany` with `include` for org + `_count` for tasks\n- `src/app/projects/[id]/page.tsx` — uses `findUnique` + `findMany` with included assignee\n- `src/app/projects/[id]/archived/page.tsx` — uses `findUnique`\n- `src/app/projects/[id]/tasks/new/page.tsx` — uses `findUnique` + `user.findMany`\n- `src/app/api/dashboard/route.ts` — Prisma count queries\n- `src/app/api/projects/route.ts` — Prisma findMany with task count\n- `src/app/api/projects/[id]/route.ts` — Prisma findUnique + findMany\n- `src/app/api/projects/[id]/tasks/route.ts` — Prisma findMany for GET, `prisma.task.create` for POST\n\nThe app builds successfully and all data now comes from PostgreSQL at `localhost:5432/afs_orm_prisma`.",
